#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_ctl.en.rst:128
msgid ""
"If this flag is provided, :option:`traffic_ctl config get` will emit "
"results in :file:`records.config` format."
msgstr ""

# 947b85caf9034ec98aab7d2a249a9a7e
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_ctl.en.rst:134
msgid ""
"Display the current values of all configuration variables whose names "
"match the given regular expression. The *--records* flag has the same "
"behavior as :option:`traffic_ctl config get --records`."
msgstr ""

# 0bf9dd36b0854fa786fafbbeb47a6c09
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_ctl.en.rst:141
msgid ""
"Initiate a Traffic Server configuration reload. Use this command to "
"update the running configuration after any configuration file "
"modification."
msgstr ""

# bee0db05fa144f219c6c871934e0ae73
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_ctl.en.rst:145
msgid ""
"The timestamp of the last reconfiguration event (in seconds since epoch) "
"is published in the `proxy.node.config.reconfigure_time` metric."
msgstr ""

# cc2898ec5f5543669340da0da83b33dd
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_ctl.en.rst:152
msgid ""
"Set the named configuration record to the specified value. Refer to the "
":file:`records.config` documentation for a list of the configuration "
"variables you can specify. Note that this is not a synchronous operation."
msgstr ""

# a56eceecd16d48ca80e21d92f3212e46
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_ctl.en.rst:160
msgid ""
"Display detailed status about the Traffic Server configuration system. "
"This includes version information, whether the internal configuration "
"store is current and whether any daemon processes should be restarted."
msgstr ""

